<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Giampaolo Rodola - new-platform</title><link>https://gmpy.dev/</link><description>Python enthusiast, core developer, psutil author</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 12 Oct 2017 00:00:00 +0200</lastBuildDate><item><title>AIX support</title><link>https://gmpy.dev/blog/2017/psutil-540-and-aix-support</link><description>&lt;p&gt;After a long wait psutil finally supports a new exotic platform: AIX!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Honestly I'm not sure how many AIX Python users are out there (probably not many), but here it is.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this we have to thank &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/wiggin15"&gt;Arnon Yaari&lt;/a&gt;, who started working on the port a couple of years ago …&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Giampaolo Rodola</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 12 Oct 2017 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:gmpy.dev,2017-10-12:/blog/2017/psutil-540-and-aix-support</guid><category>2017</category><category>psutil</category><category>python</category><category>new-platform</category><category>community</category><category>personal</category><category>release</category></item><item><title>NetBSD support</title><link>https://gmpy.dev/blog/2016/psutil-netbsd-support</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Roughly two months have passed since I last &lt;a class="reference external" href="../2015/psutil-openbsd-support"&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil"&gt;psutil&lt;/a&gt; added support for OpenBSD. Today I'm happy to announce that it's the turn of NetBSD! This was contributed by &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/0-wiz-0"&gt;Thomas Klausner&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/ryoon"&gt;Ryo Onodera&lt;/a&gt; and myself in &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil/pull/557"&gt;PR-557&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="differences-with-freebsd-and-openbsd"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Differences with FreeBSD (and OpenBSD)&lt;a class="headerlink" href="#differences-with-freebsd-and-openbsd" title="Permalink to this headline"&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NetBSD implementation has limitations similar to …&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Giampaolo Rodola</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Feb 2016 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:gmpy.dev,2016-02-25:/blog/2016/psutil-netbsd-support</guid><category>2016</category><category>psutil</category><category>python</category><category>bsd</category><category>new-platform</category><category>community</category><category>release</category></item><item><title>OpenBSD support</title><link>https://gmpy.dev/blog/2015/psutil-openbsd-support</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Starting from version 3.3.0 (released just now) &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil"&gt;psutil&lt;/a&gt; officially supports OpenBSD. This was contributed by &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/landryb"&gt;Landry Breuil&lt;/a&gt; and myself in &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil/pull/615"&gt;PR-615&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="differences-with-freebsd"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Differences with FreeBSD&lt;a class="headerlink" href="#differences-with-freebsd" title="Permalink to this headline"&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As expected, the OpenBSD implementation is very similar to FreeBSD's, so I merged most of it into a single C file (&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil/blob/release-3.3.0/psutil/_psutil_bsd.c"&gt;_psutil_bsd.c&lt;/a&gt;), with …&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Giampaolo Rodola</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 25 Nov 2015 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:gmpy.dev,2015-11-25:/blog/2015/psutil-openbsd-support</guid><category>2015</category><category>psutil</category><category>python</category><category>bsd</category><category>new-platform</category><category>community</category><category>release</category></item></channel></rss>